Palm Beach Clock Recovery Summary

Start up sequence:
  First TP found: set initial arrival time
  First PCR found: set time base offset
  Second PCR found: bit rate calculated
  First jitter measurement window completed (2500 TPs): arrival jitter measured
  (Output PSI ready)

  When all the above conditions are met, on the next PCR, output time base
  will be adjusted and locked.

PB will perform special handling under the following conditions:
  When output time base is locked at startup.
  When internal buffer overflow or underflow occurs.
  When input PCR jump is detected.
In the above cases, PB will reset the buffer fullness level to middle, and
signal PCR discontinuity at the output.

PB will resnoop PSI in the following conditions:
  When input PCR jump is detected.
  When new PAT table version is detected.
  When new PMT table version is detected.
